  "enhanced_information": "Bacterial vaginosis (BV) is a common vaginal infection characterized by an imbalance of normal vaginal flora, primarily involving anaerobic bacteria. The first-line treatment for bacterial vaginosis is Metronidazole, which is effective against these anaerobic bacteria and is well-supported by clinical guidelines. Clindamycin is an alternative treatment option but is not preferred as the first-line therapy. Erythromycin and Ampicillin are not typically used for BV and are less effective compared to Metronidazole. Therefore, the treatment of choice for bacterial vaginosis is Metronidazole."
